    name: "Srinagar Hill Palpa",
    category: "HILL_VIEWPOINT",
    summary: "Srinagar Hill rises to 1,524 metres above Tansen bazaar in Palpa district, offering one of western Nepal's finest 360-degree Himalayan panoramas. On clear days, the view sweeps from Dhaulagiri and Annapurna in the north across the green Palpa hills to the Terai plains in the south. A short hike or drive from Tansen, it is the perfect complement to a cultural visit to the historic town below.",
    story: `<h3>The Rooftop of Palpa</h3><p>Srinagar Hill crowns the ridge above Tansen, its pine and juniper-clad slopes rising less than an hour's walk above the old bazaar. The name Srinagar — 'city of beauty' — is apt: from the summit view tower, the Annapurna massif, Dhaulagiri, Manaslu, Ganesh Himal, and even the distant Langtang range string across the northern horizon like a wall of ice and rock. Below, Tansen's compact medieval roofscape merges into a tapestry of cultivated terraces and dense forest rolling south toward the Terai plains and the Indian border beyond.</p><h3>Sunrise and Sunset Magic</h3><p>The hill is Palpa's premier sunrise spot, and local visitors set out before dawn to watch the first alpenglow paint the distant snowfields. A small view tower at the summit improves sightlines over the treeline, and a Hindu shrine near the top receives steady offerings from Tansen residents. The forest cover supports leopards, jungle fowl, and a rich assortment of birdlife, making the trail up a pleasant nature walk as well as a viewpoint excursion.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li>Panoramic Himalayan views including Dhaulagiri, Annapurna, and Manaslu</li><li>Tansen town and Terai plains spread out below</li><li>Short, accessible hike or driveable road to the summit</li><li>Sunrise and sunset photography vantage point</li><li>Pine and juniper forest with resident wildlife</li></ul>`,
