    howToGetThere: "Fly from Kathmandu to Dipayal or Dhangadhi in the far west, then take a bus or jeep to Darchula town on the Mahakali River. The Api Base Camp trek begins from Darchula and takes approximately 8\u201312 days round trip. A licensed guide and proper permits are essential.",
